{{stub}}
A '''skin''' in [[ZDoom]] refers to the ability to change the sounds and sprites used by the {{Class|PlayerPawn|player avatars}} without altering the actor logic. The implementation is a compatible with the [[Doom Legacy]] implementation and uses the [[S_SKIN]] lump. To prevent conflicts with sprite or sound names, each skin [[archive format|archive]] has all its lumps put in a unique [[namespace]]; for this reason skins must be in separate files from actual mod content.
